WEBVTT

2
00:00:06.700 --> 00:00:10.360
♫ <i>Only You!  You...</i> ♫

3
00:00:10.360 --> 00:00:14.020
♫ <i>Only You!  You...</i> ♫

4
00:00:14.020 --> 00:00:18.990
♫ <i>My heart beats and I can't say anything</i> ♫

5
00:00:18.990 --> 00:00:21.790
♫ <i> I only look at you like this </i> ♫

6
00:00:21.790 --> 00:00:25.440
♫ <i>Only you!  You...</i> ♫

7
00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:29.220
♫ <i>Only you!  You...</i> ♫

8
00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:34.020
♫ <i>With a fluttering heart, I will approach you</i> ♫

9
00:00:34.020 --> 00:00:36.960
♫ <i>Open your heart a little bit to me</i> ♫

10
00:00:36.960 --> 00:00:40.060
♫ <i>Only you...</i> ♫

11
00:00:40.060 --> 00:00:42.410
<i> [Dachae Media] </i>

12
00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:50.240
Oh my.

13
00:00:57.130 --> 00:00:58.650
Thank you.

14
00:01:01.180 --> 00:01:02.870
Senior...

15
00:01:04.050 --> 00:01:06.660
The column was good!

16
00:01:06.660 --> 00:01:08.390
Same here.

17
00:01:09.220 --> 00:01:10.730
Agreed.

18
00:01:10.730 --> 00:01:13.290
These brats...

19
00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:18.290
Whether it's good or bad, we should go get scolded.

20
00:01:18.290 --> 00:01:21.820
I just arrived, so I need to sort this out a bit—

21
00:01:21.820 --> 00:01:23.570
Follow me.

22
00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:35.060
Like a magazine reporter should do, I will persuade the readers.

23
00:01:36.160 --> 00:01:40.020
Persuade? You didn't post an apology like I told you to!

24
00:01:40.020 --> 00:01:43.210
Who told you to write a diary like this?!

25
00:01:43.210 --> 00:01:45.850
Is being a reporter a joke?

26
00:01:45.850 --> 00:01:48.740
Are you looking down on the readers?!

27
00:01:48.740 --> 00:01:51.170
Are you not scared of me?

28
00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:29.240
<i>Thankfully, I didn't get in as much trouble as I thought I would.</i>

29
00:02:29.240 --> 00:02:31.800
<i>Drink up. I'll buy today.</i>

30
00:02:31.800 --> 00:02:36.290
Are you buying because I'll be unemployed tomorrow?

31
00:02:36.290 --> 00:02:39.700
I forgot my ID for job search sites.

32
00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:43.380
My resignation should help you out.

33
00:02:43.380 --> 00:02:48.670
It's not that I don't understand the company's perspective, but my life is the one that will reset if my career is interrupted.

34
00:02:48.670 --> 00:02:51.800
It's hard to get transferred somewhere as a chief editor.

35
00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:56.360
And what can I learn at this age that I can start something new?

36
00:02:56.360 --> 00:02:59.680
Are you saying... you're quitting?

37
00:03:01.070 --> 00:03:03.920
They say my baby is having febrile seizures.

38
00:03:03.920 --> 00:03:08.390
If something goes wrong, it could affect the brain, so I have to stay by her side.

39
00:03:08.390 --> 00:03:10.810
It's not serious though.

40
00:03:10.810 --> 00:03:14.350
But I'm not looking after the oldest child that well either.

41
00:03:14.350 --> 00:03:16.810
Because I forgot, my child

42
00:03:16.810 --> 00:03:19.940
slept at the childcare center for a week without a blanket.

43
00:03:19.940 --> 00:03:22.910
I was angry on top of feeling sorry.

44
00:03:24.120 --> 00:03:26.370
So I'm planning to quit.

45
00:03:28.210 --> 00:03:31.070
But... so suddenly—

46
00:03:31.070 --> 00:03:33.970
I need to quit suddenly for you to not get fired.

47
00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:37.940
You're the only one who has been loyal to "the baby" for 15 years.

48
00:03:37.940 --> 00:03:41.290
Is there anybody who has more loyalty and affection for it than you?

49
00:03:41.290 --> 00:03:44.450
How does not having a baby become a reason for disqualification?

50
00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:49.420
Even if the magazine's credibility goes up because one has a child, what's the point if you can't see your child?

51
00:03:52.430 --> 00:03:57.210
- Manager... 
 - Even if I quit, I'm going to pass over the chief editor position to you before I do.

52
00:03:57.210 --> 00:03:59.850
This is completely due to my self-interest.

53
00:03:59.850 --> 00:04:04.610
No matter how badly I treated you guys, you were the only one who understood my sincerity.

54
00:04:04.610 --> 00:04:07.760
I'd like for you to be the chief editor.

55
00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:13.530
Drink.

56
00:04:33.550 --> 00:04:38.910
<i>There was no curative effects last time, but would you still like to try?</i>

57
00:04:49.050 --> 00:04:51.590
<i>What if you come to love someone?</i>

58
00:04:51.590 --> 00:04:55.350
<i>Have you never thought about wanting to be a father?</i>

59
00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:58.240
<i> I never did.</i>

60
00:04:59.680 --> 00:05:02.930
<i> Who knew that I'd hurt this much because of you?</i>

61
00:05:19.400 --> 00:05:23.590
<i>Stop it!</i>

62
00:05:24.450 --> 00:05:28.920
<i>- Ow! 
 - Let go! Stop it!</i>

63
00:05:39.920 --> 00:05:42.210
Han Yisang!

64
00:06:00.330 --> 00:06:02.170
What are you doing?

65
00:06:07.770 --> 00:06:10.440
I wish you'd be a little more pleased to see me...

66
00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:14.190
It looks like you want to be alone, so I'll go.

67
00:06:15.630 --> 00:06:17.660
Don't go.

68
00:06:20.070 --> 00:06:22.340
Do you want to talk with me?

69
00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:25.650
Okay.

70
00:06:30.160 --> 00:06:32.310
What'd you do today?

71
00:06:34.970 --> 00:06:38.900
Living is like homework, so I was trying to solve it.

72
00:06:39.810 --> 00:06:45.000
I want to get the answer right, but it's hard.

73
00:06:45.000 --> 00:06:50.250
Oh, that's very deep. Looks like my question was philosophical.

74
00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:54.000
"Well, after finishing work and idly lying around,

75
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:57.740
I went out for a walk in the park, but suddenly thought about Jang Hari."

76
00:06:57.740 --> 00:07:00.530
I thought you'd give an answer like that.

77
00:07:01.290 --> 00:07:03.610
Why would you think about me?

78
00:07:07.470 --> 00:07:09.380
Right.

79
00:07:09.380 --> 00:07:14.060
Why did I... think of you?

80
00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:21.470
Well, you could!

81
00:07:21.470 --> 00:07:26.620
We've bumped into each other a lot here, and as a fellow resident of this neighborhood, you could suddenly wonder what I'm doing,

82
00:07:26.620 --> 00:07:31.160
whether or not I'm coming out for a walk... you could be curious.

83
00:07:31.160 --> 00:07:33.930
I was thinking what a strange person you were.

84
00:07:33.930 --> 00:07:38.550
Usually, people will pretend to not be hurt even if they are,

85
00:07:38.550 --> 00:07:43.530
will hide their scars, and cover up their weaknesses.

86
00:07:44.260 --> 00:07:47.630
But... when I look at you,

87
00:07:47.630 --> 00:07:54.080
I become embarrassed of myself for trying so hard to pretend to be strong.

88
00:07:57.740 --> 00:08:00.930
Like asking a man that you don't really like

89
00:08:00.930 --> 00:08:05.210
to marry, the shock was big.

90
00:08:06.900 --> 00:08:12.310
How... could you confess to the world?

91
00:08:12.310 --> 00:08:15.250
You're brave, Jang Hari.

92
00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:23.000
I'm saying this because I'm drunk, but...

93
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:28.130
Jang Hari... you did well.

94
00:08:36.080 --> 00:08:40.870
This is... instead of a stamp.

95
00:09:02.670 --> 00:09:06.840
Because of you, my heart feels very soft and fuzzy.

96
00:09:06.840 --> 00:09:10.920
Thank you... for noticing.

97
00:09:14.750 --> 00:09:16.130
Mother!

98
00:09:16.130 --> 00:09:19.410
Oh? Yisang!

99
00:09:19.410 --> 00:09:21.530
Go carefully.

100
00:09:22.650 --> 00:09:25.300
Why did you come without contacting me?

101
00:09:25.300 --> 00:09:29.500
Why would I? I know you're busy.

102
00:09:29.500 --> 00:09:33.390
I left the fermented flatfish with the security office.

103
00:09:33.390 --> 00:09:37.170
But... who's that?

104
00:09:39.340 --> 00:09:42.460
- Hello. 
 - Ah, yes, nice to meet you.

105
00:09:42.460 --> 00:09:45.820
She's a coworker. Let's go inside.

106
00:09:46.900 --> 00:09:50.390
I... I'm not really curious about your house.

107
00:09:50.390 --> 00:09:53.610
Let go of me. Let go.

108
00:09:53.610 --> 00:09:56.980
What's your name?

109
00:09:56.980 --> 00:09:58.720
I'm Jang Hari.

110
00:09:58.720 --> 00:10:00.550
Hari!

111
00:10:00.550 --> 00:10:04.620
Wow! Her name is as pretty as her face.

112
00:10:04.620 --> 00:10:06.610
Thank you.

113
00:10:07.460 --> 00:10:10.140
You should go.

114
00:10:10.140 --> 00:10:13.010
- Mother, I'll escort you. 
 - To where?

115
00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:15.340
Let go, let go!

116
00:10:15.340 --> 00:10:19.130
It looks like you're coming back from being out together.

117
00:10:20.650 --> 00:10:22.550
Don't worry.

118
00:10:22.550 --> 00:10:26.060
I... barely go to his house.

119
00:10:26.060 --> 00:10:29.150
So you can come anytime and have fun in a comfortable manner.

120
00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:31.210
No. That...

121
00:10:31.210 --> 00:10:33.040
We're not that type of relation, Mother.

122
00:10:33.040 --> 00:10:34.950
Ex-Excuse me, you should go. I'm sorry.

123
00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:37.040
- Hey, hey, you did well. 
 - Mom!

124
00:10:37.040 --> 00:10:39.230
- You did well. 
 - Please don't be like that.

125
00:10:39.230 --> 00:10:41.110
- Let go of me for a bit. 
 - M-Mother!

126
00:10:41.110 --> 00:10:44.090
- Aigoo, Mom, you should go inside and— 
 - I like him!

127
00:10:44.090 --> 00:10:46.410
- Huh? 
 - That's right.

128
00:10:49.470 --> 00:10:52.360
I... like Han Yisang.

129
00:10:58.310 --> 00:10:59.880
Is that so?

130
00:10:59.880 --> 00:11:02.330
So... don't worry.

131
00:11:02.330 --> 00:11:05.260
Y-Y-Yes. Aigoo.

132
00:11:05.260 --> 00:11:08.590
Aigoo, thank you. Thank you.

133
00:11:10.830 --> 00:11:13.650
The taxi is coming. Let's meet again later.

134
00:11:13.650 --> 00:11:16.500
Goodbye.

135
00:11:16.500 --> 00:11:20.210
Yisang! I'm going!

136
00:12:03.830 --> 00:12:05.550
- Why? 
 - Did you eat?

137
00:12:05.550 --> 00:12:07.530
Are you crazy? Do you know what time it is?

138
00:12:07.530 --> 00:12:09.550
- Have you had intestines? 
 - Why are you talking about intestines?

139
00:12:09.550 --> 00:12:12.150
I'm craving them, but they don't come in single servings.

140
00:12:12.150 --> 00:12:13.370
I said I already ate.

141
00:12:13.370 --> 00:12:14.880
So have some intestines.

142
00:12:14.880 --> 00:12:18.420
Go on up, wash, and sleep. I stopped eating intestines.

143
00:12:36.420 --> 00:12:39.210
<i>Did I do something wrong?</i>

144
00:12:46.350 --> 00:12:49.550
<i>Why is it all so easy for you?</i>

145
00:12:49.550 --> 00:12:52.340
<i>No, it seemed like your mother was worrying too much, so—</i>

146
00:12:52.340 --> 00:12:55.580
<i>Can you fall in love just by looking at someone?</i>

147
00:12:55.580 --> 00:12:57.510
<i>We aren't that—</i>

148
00:12:59.270 --> 00:13:01.050
<i>We're not young.</i>

149
00:13:01.050 --> 00:13:04.970
<i> If we're not able to accept each other, we shouldn't start it.</i>

150
00:13:06.980 --> 00:13:09.780
<i>Why is it so complicated?</i>

151
00:13:13.170 --> 00:13:15.230
<i>Because I know the ending.</i>

152
00:13:17.920 --> 00:13:23.270
<i>You... want a child.</i>

153
00:13:27.070 --> 00:13:30.190
<i>I don't.</i>

154
00:13:31.110 --> 00:13:36.790
<i>You getting hurt... I can't take responsibility for it.</i>

155
00:13:36.790 --> 00:13:38.710
<i>Han Yisang...</i>

156
00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:44.620
<i>I take responsibility for my own heart. </i>

157
00:13:50.890 --> 00:13:54.610
<i> It seems I made a mistake because my feelings got ahead of me.</i>

158
00:13:55.400 --> 00:14:01.020
<i>So that I don't misunderstand in the future, please be careful, too. </i>

159
00:14:26.050 --> 00:14:28.630
It must be the signs of a wretched fate.

160
00:14:29.490 --> 00:14:30.690
You said you weren't going to eat.

161
00:14:30.690 --> 00:14:32.380
You should have asked me to have a drink.

162
00:14:32.380 --> 00:14:34.600
But I'm not going to drink.

163
00:14:35.750 --> 00:14:38.830
How can you eat intestines without drinking soju?

164
00:14:38.830 --> 00:14:40.370
I'll get drunk.

165
00:14:40.370 --> 00:14:45.660
I don't know who it is, but a man who makes you worry isn't it.

166
00:14:47.050 --> 00:14:48.420
What man?

167
00:14:48.420 --> 00:14:50.550
If not, then never mind.

168
00:14:54.690 --> 00:14:59.710
Getting excited over that small thing... I was the only one.

169
00:15:01.430 --> 00:15:02.440
That?

170
00:15:02.440 --> 00:15:06.750
I had firmly made up my mind that I didn't need a man.

171
00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:12.590
To lose rationality over that paltry little moment...

172
00:15:16.610 --> 00:15:19.900
Perhaps... a kiss?

173
00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:25.110
I lost my judgment since I haven't done it for a long time.

174
00:15:25.110 --> 00:15:28.170
You slept with him?!

175
00:15:28.170 --> 00:15:30.310
What nonsense are you spouting?

176
00:15:30.310 --> 00:15:32.800
Quiet down!

177
00:15:36.060 --> 00:15:40.070
If you didn't sleep with him, then never mind. I got so shocked.

178
00:15:40.070 --> 00:15:42.820
With just a touch

179
00:15:44.620 --> 00:15:49.460
or a gaze, I become captivated. Even though I'm 40 soon.

180
00:15:50.490 --> 00:15:53.510
I think it's best for you to live alone.

181
00:16:01.510 --> 00:16:04.640
Why are you giving your whole heart away to a man who doesn't do anything?

182
00:16:04.640 --> 00:16:06.910
Retrieve your heart.

183
00:16:10.530 --> 00:16:13.170
It would've been different if we had been 20, right?

184
00:16:13.170 --> 00:16:18.080
Even if we had met at 30, he wouldn't have been this hesitant.

185
00:16:20.640 --> 00:16:23.640
Like how I don't have time...

186
00:16:24.710 --> 00:16:26.820
he probably has a complicated reason.

187
00:16:26.820 --> 00:16:28.780
Why are you trying to understand him?!

188
00:16:28.780 --> 00:16:33.790
What's so important about that man's situation?! You said you didn't have time.

189
00:16:36.080 --> 00:16:40.890
You punk. Why didn't you talk to me when I'm a doctor?

190
00:16:40.890 --> 00:16:43.900
I didn't know pediatricians could deal with infertility.

191
00:16:43.900 --> 00:16:46.740
We can all do counseling.

192
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:50.140
Ah, seriously.

193
00:16:51.050 --> 00:16:55.350
So what are you feeling? You said you didn't have time to date and then marry.

194
00:16:55.350 --> 00:16:58.870
You said you've never been happy because of a man before in your life.

195
00:17:02.870 --> 00:17:05.190
You still want to have expectations?

196
00:17:06.560 --> 00:17:10.690
It's because I'm trying to fold my expectations that I'm hurting.

197
00:17:14.860 --> 00:17:18.130
It would've been nice if I was 20 today.

198
00:17:19.940 --> 00:17:23.060
So that I could at least try hanging onto him for giving me butterflies.

199
00:17:30.030 --> 00:17:38.690
<i>[Episode 7: The Right Amount of Space to Prevent Heartbreak]</i>

200
00:17:43.760 --> 00:17:47.830
You can just take the background out of focus.

201
00:17:47.830 --> 00:17:51.010
There's no background to take out of focus.

202
00:17:51.010 --> 00:17:52.540
Are you insisting because you don't know?

203
00:17:52.540 --> 00:17:56.510
Don't you think we can do something like this with the props we have over there?

204
00:17:56.510 --> 00:17:59.330
Isn't that up to your ability?

205
00:18:00.240 --> 00:18:05.670
Bring in the right props first then. I don't need you to judge my ability to take photos, Reporter Choi.

206
00:18:05.670 --> 00:18:09.840
You sure make your work difficult when you can just take the photos as ordered.

207
00:18:09.840 --> 00:18:14.060
Reporter Choi, let's keep our basic manners while working.

208
00:18:14.060 --> 00:18:18.300
Looking down on others hardly hides your own lack of talent.

209
00:18:18.300 --> 00:18:20.320
Chief Han.

210
00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:26.970
Take the pictures by how the reporter in charge wants it.

211
00:18:36.030 --> 00:18:40.760
From planning the article to getting the pictorial's concept to preparing the props, Reporter Choi did everything.

212
00:18:40.760 --> 00:18:44.970
We'll make the final decision after seeing how the photos come out.

213
00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:48.240
If we have to re-shoot, then you're uselessly working twice.

214
00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:53.610
- Can the editing team use the photographing department's time and effort so thoughtlessly? 
 - That also...

215
00:18:53.610 --> 00:18:57.650
leave that decision up to the reporter in charge.

216
00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:04.580
- Take care of it, please. 
 - Okay.

217
00:19:14.050 --> 00:19:17.640
I took your side so that you could take responsibility.

218
00:19:17.640 --> 00:19:20.130
You know it, right? That you did wrong?

219
00:19:20.130 --> 00:19:24.300
I couldn't let him have the upper hand when he's just an outside hire.

220
00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:26.610
No matter how in-demand he is,

221
00:19:26.610 --> 00:19:29.960
shouldn't he listen to the reporter?

222
00:19:29.960 --> 00:19:32.540
Do you see me as your superior?

223
00:19:33.850 --> 00:19:37.810
The photography and art teams are our partners, not underlings.

224
00:19:39.830 --> 00:19:42.630
I feel sorry toward you.

225
00:19:42.630 --> 00:19:47.190
Because I was afraid of being called an oldie, I didn't teach you the things that I should have.

226
00:19:47.190 --> 00:19:50.650
Since it's obvious you won't like listening to me saying "do this, do that, don't do it."

227
00:19:50.650 --> 00:19:54.270
My assumption that you would just learn by our example was a failure to do my duty.

228
00:19:55.050 --> 00:19:57.960
I... don't plan on working here for a long time.

229
00:19:57.960 --> 00:20:01.560
I know. You job search every day.

230
00:20:02.240 --> 00:20:04.790
Is that why you're just doing your work half-ass?

231
00:20:04.790 --> 00:20:08.580
I've never done my work half-ass. I try and do well.

232
00:20:08.580 --> 00:20:12.240
Instead of pretending to do well, you should actually do well.

233
00:20:12.240 --> 00:20:16.800
Working without pride will make the workplace seem like hell.

234
00:20:16.800 --> 00:20:21.670
I'm going to start saying things you won't like. I also won't say things like, "This is enough."

235
00:20:21.670 --> 00:20:24.910
Until you produce better results, I won't stop hounding you.

236
00:20:24.910 --> 00:20:28.820
So that wherever you go, you'll receive an acknowledgment from what you learned here.

237
00:20:32.180 --> 00:20:37.540
You can quit once you make a portfolio that you can show others proudly.

238
00:20:40.140 --> 00:20:42.250
<i>Let's take a break.</i>

239
00:20:50.030 --> 00:20:52.920
I picked the photo for the infertile couple.

240
00:20:55.910 --> 00:21:00.200
They must have seen and learned from my frank manner of speaking to you.

241
00:21:00.200 --> 00:21:02.940
I'm sorry I let them act thoughtlessly.

242
00:21:09.540 --> 00:21:11.270
Okay.

243
00:21:15.100 --> 00:21:19.310
Because of me...

244
00:21:19.310 --> 00:21:24.640
I hope that your feelings haven't been hurt.

245
00:21:27.710 --> 00:21:30.910
<i> It seems I made a mistake because my feelings got ahead of me.</i>

246
00:21:30.910 --> 00:21:36.690
<i>So that I don't misunderstand in the future, please be careful, too. </i>

247
00:21:58.980 --> 00:22:00.680
I...

248
00:22:02.110 --> 00:22:08.210
broke off the engagement with a longtime girlfriend.

249
00:22:08.210 --> 00:22:16.010
And... gave up on getting married. And a baby is not in my life.

250
00:22:16.770 --> 00:22:22.610
I didn't want my heart to flutter, but you began to sway me.

251
00:22:22.610 --> 00:22:28.190
My actions were unclear, and it's understandable why you took it the wrong way.

252
00:22:29.490 --> 00:22:31.940
In the end, it was a misunderstanding.

253
00:22:31.940 --> 00:22:34.660
I thought about it for a short time,

254
00:22:35.720 --> 00:22:39.430
but I still like being alone.

255
00:22:39.430 --> 00:22:43.350
I've thought about living alone for a long time,

256
00:22:43.350 --> 00:22:46.540
so I've decided on the path that my life will take.

257
00:22:53.940 --> 00:22:56.160
I'm sorry...

258
00:22:58.410 --> 00:23:00.340
for confusing you.

259
00:23:02.970 --> 00:23:05.810
I'll accept your apology.

260
00:23:05.810 --> 00:23:08.500
You said you didn't want your heart to flutter, right? Same here.

261
00:23:08.500 --> 00:23:12.390
Even though it was for a short time, I was uncomfortable having complicated feelings.

262
00:23:15.100 --> 00:23:16.500
Let's see each other comfortably.

263
00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:19.240
Okay. Sure.

264
00:23:28.140 --> 00:23:32.650
<i>[Jambi Studio]</i>

265
00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:40.740
♫ <i>A cold season passes by</i> ♫

266
00:23:43.840 --> 00:23:48.400
♫ <i>You, the one I've waited for, are coming</i> ♫

267
00:23:51.650 --> 00:23:56.360
♫ <i>At the end of a long day</i> ♫

268
00:23:59.390 --> 00:24:04.110
♫ <i>You're still standing there</i> ♫

269
00:24:07.070 --> 00:24:14.590
♫ <i>Like the stars, your name enters my heart</i> ♫

270
00:24:14.590 --> 00:24:20.930
♫ <i>I try calling it one last time</i> ♫

271
00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:28.960
♫ <i>I'm still with you, in the same moment</i> ♫

272
00:24:30.780 --> 00:24:36.420
♫ <i>I'm still with you, I want to stay by your side</i> ♫

273
00:24:38.520 --> 00:24:44.120
♫ <i>Goodbye, all my painful days, goodbye </i>♫

274
00:24:44.120 --> 00:24:51.600
<i> - Wow, so cool.</i>
♫ <i> ...all my lonely days, now and forever...</i> ♫

275
00:25:12.240 --> 00:25:13.220
<i>[The Right Toothpaste For My Child]</i>

276
00:25:13.220 --> 00:25:14.660
Is it all like this?

277
00:25:14.660 --> 00:25:16.810
Why are they like this?

278
00:25:16.810 --> 00:25:20.850
Is this the first time you've bartered for anything? These expire in just six months.

279
00:25:20.850 --> 00:25:24.180
Looks like they dumped unwanted product on us, so what do you intend to do?

280
00:25:24.180 --> 00:25:27.250
He's a newcomer. Go easy on him.

281
00:25:27.250 --> 00:25:30.670
I was talking to you.

282
00:25:30.670 --> 00:25:32.420
Oh, right.

283
00:25:32.420 --> 00:25:37.080
Didn't you ask the advertising team to check the expiration dates?

284
00:25:37.080 --> 00:25:40.390
No, that... I...

285
00:25:40.390 --> 00:25:43.230
I was going to...

286
00:25:50.460 --> 00:25:54.910
I heard it but forgot. I'm sorry.

287
00:25:58.470 --> 00:26:03.610
We can't send this out as a giveaway to readers. Go get another batch.

288
00:26:03.610 --> 00:26:08.390
How are we going to return these? It was hard to get these—

289
00:26:11.360 --> 00:26:15.010
Let's do it with words, not talk with your eyes.

290
00:26:15.010 --> 00:26:19.210
Figure it out yourself, and get the new ones here.

291
00:26:19.210 --> 00:26:21.080
Okay.

292
00:26:24.960 --> 00:26:26.250
You understand, right?

293
00:26:26.250 --> 00:26:27.790
Yes.

294
00:26:32.240 --> 00:26:34.030
Bye.

295
00:26:35.650 --> 00:26:37.830
Yes, I got it.

296
00:26:38.710 --> 00:26:40.330
Goodbye.

297
00:26:54.180 --> 00:27:00.350
I was going to tell them, but I was so surprised from the fake slippers that I forgot.

298
00:27:01.500 --> 00:27:04.210
I see.

299
00:27:04.210 --> 00:27:08.620
But... did you help me out earlier?

300
00:27:11.690 --> 00:27:14.920
I thought it would be best if you didn't get in trouble.

301
00:27:14.920 --> 00:27:19.800
It seemed like you were scolded earlier. So if you were to get scolded again, I thought you'd be very angry.

302
00:27:19.800 --> 00:27:22.650
But... why do you keep getting told off?

303
00:27:22.650 --> 00:27:24.820
I get told off 'cause I'm new.

304
00:27:24.820 --> 00:27:27.540
I wasn't told off!

305
00:27:28.500 --> 00:27:31.160
You just have a lot of anger, I see.

306
00:27:33.120 --> 00:27:37.740
But... I was only going to say hello since you told me to,

307
00:27:37.740 --> 00:27:41.980
but you keep talking to me first.

308
00:27:43.130 --> 00:27:47.400
Are you... arguing about me talking to you first right now?

309
00:27:47.400 --> 00:27:53.050
No, no, no. More than just saying hello, I like it better when we talk.

310
00:27:53.930 --> 00:27:58.050
Then... shall we talk longer next time?

311
00:27:58.050 --> 00:28:01.620
I'll be going. Fighting!

312
00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:08.600
That's a confession, right?

313
00:28:09.560 --> 00:28:12.500
Why does he confess like that?

314
00:28:21.410 --> 00:28:27.130
What is that smile? It really offends me. What are you asking for?

315
00:28:27.130 --> 00:28:28.220
To eat.

316
00:28:28.220 --> 00:28:30.540
Why would you come all the way here and buy me food?

317
00:28:30.540 --> 00:28:33.920
Because I hate eating alone. Let's go.

318
00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:37.390
You look like you're scheming something.

319
00:28:37.390 --> 00:28:39.270
Hurry up and come!

320
00:28:44.700 --> 00:28:46.310
Here.

321
00:28:48.330 --> 00:28:49.220
I don't have money.

322
00:28:49.220 --> 00:28:52.180
I don't have time either. I can't do anything.

323
00:28:52.180 --> 00:28:55.360
I came to just eat a meal together.

324
00:28:55.360 --> 00:28:58.730
Relax your eyes and let's enjoy the food.

325
00:28:58.730 --> 00:29:02.390
I've thought about it after putting our 39 years of friendship on the line...

326
00:29:02.390 --> 00:29:04.200
Are you a terminally ill patient?

327
00:29:04.200 --> 00:29:09.250
If so, I have no reason to not make your last wish come true.

328
00:29:10.620 --> 00:29:12.630
I'll marry you.

329
00:29:17.580 --> 00:29:21.780
Five minutes. No, think about it for a minute.

330
00:29:21.780 --> 00:29:22.580
It tastes good.

331
00:29:22.580 --> 00:29:25.380
At least pretend to think about it.

332
00:29:29.960 --> 00:29:32.290
<i>Honey, is the food almost ready?</i>

333
00:29:32.290 --> 00:29:35.430
<i>- Did you launder my socks? 
 - Socks?</i>

334
00:29:35.430 --> 00:29:39.280
<i>I need my white shirt to be ironed stiffly for tomorrow.</i>

335
00:29:39.280 --> 00:29:43.610
<i>I'm going to take a bath after eating, so set the water's temperature to 39.5 degrees Celsius. </i>

336
00:29:43.610 --> 00:29:47.690
<i> I'm a bit sensitive.</i>

337
00:29:47.690 --> 00:29:51.480
I've lost my appetite. Just hire a nice housekeeper!

338
00:29:51.480 --> 00:29:54.110
Why do you hate it that much? Is it that much of a "no"?

339
00:29:54.110 --> 00:29:55.580
Then, did you think it would be a yes?

340
00:29:55.580 --> 00:29:59.060
I'm thankful that you're worried for me, but why put our friendship on the line?

341
00:29:59.060 --> 00:30:03.360
What's wrong with you lately? Am I that pitiful?

342
00:30:03.360 --> 00:30:06.690
I... these days...

343
00:30:13.750 --> 00:30:16.120
am lonely.

344
00:30:16.120 --> 00:30:19.820
Is it andropause? Do you feel lonely all of a sudden, feel empty without any reason, and feel like crying?

345
00:30:19.820 --> 00:30:25.390
It's closer to puberty. Swinging from dislike to like, and feeling irritable all of a sudden.

346
00:30:28.240 --> 00:30:33.860
That's why you have to look after me, so I don't go astray.

347
00:30:40.260 --> 00:30:43.220
I'm looking at you now. Eat.

348
00:30:45.030 --> 00:30:48.190
Thoroughly chew and eat. You'll get indigestion.

349
00:30:52.930 --> 00:30:55.680
Wait in here, please.

350
00:30:55.680 --> 00:30:59.020
I don't know when the team leader will be back either.

351
00:30:59.950 --> 00:31:02.960
She'll probably be here before she gets fired.

352
00:31:02.960 --> 00:31:04.560
Ah, yeah...

353
00:31:13.560 --> 00:31:15.350
<i>[Resignation Form]</i>

354
00:31:15.350 --> 00:31:18.580
<i>[I am no longer able to fulfill my work obligations due to childcare needs.] </i>

355
00:31:32.950 --> 00:31:35.780
I wasn't telling you to resign,

356
00:31:35.780 --> 00:31:38.660
more like temporary retirement.

357
00:31:38.660 --> 00:31:41.550
That, to me, are words for resignation.

358
00:31:41.550 --> 00:31:44.640
And... it's about time for me to quit.

359
00:31:44.640 --> 00:31:47.950
I should leave my spot for the younger ones to get promoted.

360
00:31:50.830 --> 00:31:54.020
It's not like I can hold onto you since your child is sick.

361
00:31:54.020 --> 00:31:57.800
Then... can you keep on coming till we find a replacement?

362
00:31:57.800 --> 00:31:59.300
No.

363
00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:03.550
I'm going to transfer my position to Deputy Editor Jang and quit right away.

364
00:32:06.000 --> 00:32:09.120
Resigning suddenly like this

365
00:32:09.120 --> 00:32:14.830
doesn't mean she'll automatically be promoted to chief editor. Acting chief editor, at most.

366
00:32:22.860 --> 00:32:27.760
I also... treasure Deputy Editor Jang.

367
00:32:27.760 --> 00:32:33.800
But the chairman's rage is so big that it'll be hard for Deputy Jang.

368
00:32:33.800 --> 00:32:39.330
So... you should stay here until we find a replacement.

369
00:32:39.330 --> 00:32:40.830
Okay.

370
00:32:43.560 --> 00:32:45.990
Have a good day.

371
00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:50.480
Hey, Joo Seungtae. 
 <i>(T/N: informal manner)</i>

372
00:32:52.410 --> 00:32:59.750
Be a loyal dog to the chairman, or take care of your subordinates. Pick one of the two.

373
00:32:59.750 --> 00:33:03.180
Or do both well.

374
00:33:03.180 --> 00:33:05.540
Have a good day!

375
00:33:24.030 --> 00:33:25.270
You were here?

376
00:33:25.270 --> 00:33:27.790
You didn't leave yet?

377
00:33:27.790 --> 00:33:30.840
I was at Cheonwang all day,

378
00:33:30.840 --> 00:33:35.950
and couldn't see Team Leader Park. So I'm still here 'cause I didn't do anything today.

379
00:33:37.130 --> 00:33:39.870
Were you just blindly waiting?

380
00:33:39.870 --> 00:33:41.550
Did Manager Kim order you?

381
00:33:41.550 --> 00:33:44.260
It's my work, so I have to figure it out.

382
00:33:45.850 --> 00:33:49.960
Deputy Editor, I learned a lot from your column.

383
00:33:49.960 --> 00:33:52.830
Learning is a bit...

384
00:33:52.830 --> 00:33:55.740
- I should do well to maintain my private life. 
 - Hey.

385
00:33:56.780 --> 00:34:00.080
I also need to be more courageous.

386
00:34:02.690 --> 00:34:05.620
I'm too young to determine if it was right or wrong,

387
00:34:05.620 --> 00:34:09.720
I just think you're amazing.

388
00:34:09.720 --> 00:34:11.930
About what?

389
00:34:11.930 --> 00:34:17.860
I'm not sure about what I want to do, so I'm just floating about right now.

390
00:34:17.860 --> 00:34:22.690
But you know exactly what you want.

391
00:34:22.690 --> 00:34:24.460
You're living your life.

392
00:34:24.460 --> 00:34:27.490
And it may be something that others might have never thought of,

393
00:34:27.490 --> 00:34:32.120
and it could be something that someone has thought about but couldn't do.

394
00:34:32.120 --> 00:34:33.890
You're cool.

395
00:34:35.890 --> 00:34:40.280
You're able to understand me?

396
00:34:40.280 --> 00:34:43.600
Yes. Your dream isn't illegal.

397
00:34:47.910 --> 00:34:48.900
Go inside.

398
00:34:48.900 --> 00:34:51.140
Okay. Work hard.

399
00:34:58.130 --> 00:35:01.010
<i>[Advertising Team: CHOIKANG EUTTEUM]</i>

400
00:35:07.280 --> 00:35:09.320
What brings you here, Reporter Choi?

401
00:35:09.320 --> 00:35:10.870
I'm exactly like Chow Yun Fat, right?

402
00:35:10.870 --> 00:35:13.530
Wh- what fat?

403
00:35:13.530 --> 00:35:15.680
She doesn't know.

404
00:35:15.680 --> 00:35:18.780
Has Mr. Eutteum not come to work yet?

405
00:35:18.780 --> 00:35:20.670
He left for work to Cheonan.

406
00:35:20.670 --> 00:35:23.750
Team Leader Park there... He's really something else.

407
00:35:23.750 --> 00:35:27.340
If it's not beneficial for them, they don't pick up the phone or meet up with you.

408
00:35:27.340 --> 00:35:30.640
You sent Eutteum to that place?

409
00:35:30.650 --> 00:35:33.370
Why? Can I not send him?

410
00:35:33.370 --> 00:35:37.850
Euttuem isn't someone who'll come back with something. He'll get scammed.

411
00:35:38.660 --> 00:35:41.400
You're sure saying nonsense.

412
00:35:41.400 --> 00:35:43.170
Why is she...?

413
00:35:47.540 --> 00:35:48.470
Yes, Hyojoo?

414
00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:51.760
Are you going to keep on being there?

415
00:35:51.760 --> 00:35:53.260
I'll have to wait. It's my work.

416
00:35:53.260 --> 00:35:56.280
Don't be like that and come back quickly!

417
00:35:56.280 --> 00:35:58.240
What's going on?

418
00:35:58.240 --> 00:36:01.420
No, I said there's something.

419
00:36:01.420 --> 00:36:06.800
There's this, there's that. There's so much to do, so you should hurry and come back.

420
00:36:12.450 --> 00:36:15.710
Who is it? Eutteum?

421
00:36:15.710 --> 00:36:18.760
Yes. He's still in Cheonan.

422
00:36:18.760 --> 00:36:24.290
He's so innocent. The guy won't even meet with him. He's indefinitely waiting.

423
00:36:24.290 --> 00:36:27.600
Why did he send Eutteum to such a place?

424
00:36:27.600 --> 00:36:31.840
Anyway, isn't this not it?

425
00:36:31.840 --> 00:36:35.930
Yeonwoo, did Cheonwang's proposal come out yet?

426
00:36:35.930 --> 00:36:37.780
Just a second.

427
00:36:42.110 --> 00:36:44.930
Is there a meeting? I reserved this room for 11.

428
00:36:44.930 --> 00:36:49.420
No, go ahead.

429
00:36:52.080 --> 00:36:54.280
Work hard. Work hard.

430
00:37:04.380 --> 00:37:09.460
I got your project proposition from Reporter Park. I don't think anything will be problematic.

431
00:37:11.100 --> 00:37:12.860
Uh...

432
00:37:20.270 --> 00:37:22.220
Eutteum.

433
00:37:23.270 --> 00:37:28.380
Oh? Why are you here, Deputy Editor?

434
00:37:29.560 --> 00:37:33.220
But the problem is right here.

435
00:37:36.930 --> 00:37:41.320
Are subcontractors supposed to shut up and just do as they're told while being punished here like this?

436
00:37:41.320 --> 00:37:43.590
We weren't punishing him, but—

437
00:37:43.590 --> 00:37:48.740
When you're a newcomer, you're always wary of your superiors and worry about all the mistakes you've made today.

438
00:37:48.740 --> 00:37:53.000
And punish yourself wondering if you should be turning in a resignation letter.

439
00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:59.750
They already get overwhelmed by the printer. They shouldn't have to worry about not receiving common courtesy from their coworkers.

440
00:38:01.420 --> 00:38:02.930
I apologize.

441
00:38:02.930 --> 00:38:06.280
We were busy and inconsiderate of you.

442
00:38:10.570 --> 00:38:11.930
Yes, Sir.

443
00:38:11.930 --> 00:38:15.070
PD, you guys are leaving the work to us because you trust us. Right?

444
00:38:15.070 --> 00:38:18.770
We believe that we have a trusting relationship with Cheonwang.

445
00:38:18.770 --> 00:38:22.380
Let's keep getting along.

446
00:38:24.460 --> 00:38:26.480
I'll put you through to the team leader right away.

447
00:38:26.480 --> 00:38:28.450
Thank you.

448
00:38:29.630 --> 00:38:32.190
Team Leader, just a moment.

449
00:38:34.180 --> 00:38:38.300
Hello, this is Deputy Editor Jang Hari from "the baby."

450
00:38:38.300 --> 00:38:40.470
I came because of the toothpaste,

451
00:38:40.470 --> 00:38:44.200
but it seems like you're quite busy, so maybe I should just bring the matter to the chairman...

452
00:38:44.200 --> 00:38:47.780
or maybe I could head up to the president's office?

453
00:39:03.660 --> 00:39:05.030
<i> Wow, you've done it!</i>

454
00:39:05.030 --> 00:39:08.300
Oh! Chief!

455
00:39:08.300 --> 00:39:09.430
Han Yisang?

456
00:39:09.430 --> 00:39:11.750
- Aren't you happy to see me?
 - Yeah.

457
00:39:11.750 --> 00:39:13.430
What an over-the-top greeting.

458
00:39:13.430 --> 00:39:14.970
You made a lot of money.

459
00:39:14.970 --> 00:39:16.790
I did.

460
00:39:16.790 --> 00:39:18.030
- Have you been well? 
 - Of course.

461
00:39:18.030 --> 00:39:24.340
He's not only at peace but laughs? Wow, he ignores my lips but hugs her like that?

462
00:39:27.270 --> 00:39:32.230
I'm feeling nervous since I'm making a comeback after such a long time.

463
00:39:32.230 --> 00:39:35.660
Maybe it's because you became a mother, but your aura became a lot softer.

464
00:39:35.660 --> 00:39:37.450
Really?

465
00:39:37.450 --> 00:39:39.320
You look a lot better.

466
00:39:43.480 --> 00:39:46.030
Oh my, you were here.

467
00:39:50.900 --> 00:39:53.080
Oh my, you were here.

468
00:39:53.080 --> 00:39:59.380
I... drink fresh juice after eating my meal, you see.

469
00:40:00.220 --> 00:40:05.410
Ah... this is "the baby" magazine's Jang Hari.

470
00:40:05.410 --> 00:40:07.420
You know her, right? Kang Yoojoo.

471
00:40:07.420 --> 00:40:09.770
- Kang Yoojoo. Yes, yes. 
 - Hello.

472
00:40:09.770 --> 00:40:15.940
- It's nice to meet you. 
 - Chief Han Yisang and I are colleagues who are very comfortable with each other.

473
00:40:15.940 --> 00:40:18.700
I think it'll be great if you could be in our magazine one day.

474
00:40:18.700 --> 00:40:20.460
It'll be good!

475
00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:23.880
Don't mind me and talk comfortably among yourselves.

476
00:40:24.790 --> 00:40:27.020
She has a very bright personality.

477
00:40:27.020 --> 00:40:32.190
She looks like it. Speaking of, I got a pictorial offer.

478
00:40:32.190 --> 00:40:36.470
I feel all this pressure. I've had two kids now and people are going to start talking.

479
00:40:36.470 --> 00:40:42.230
That after all this time, my figure is saggy and my face is haggard. It would be the worst!

480
00:40:42.230 --> 00:40:44.800
Pressure?

481
00:40:44.800 --> 00:40:48.840
Back then or right now, Kang Yoojoo is at the top.

482
00:41:03.750 --> 00:41:05.870
And that's precisely why I'm saying this.

483
00:41:08.600 --> 00:41:12.760
You should take my pictures.

484
00:41:12.760 --> 00:41:17.450
I wouldn't be "taking" anything. It'll be an honor for me.

485
00:41:17.450 --> 00:41:22.580
You know how much I like you. Please take the photos for me.

486
00:41:22.580 --> 00:41:25.010
I really want you to take them.

487
00:41:25.020 --> 00:41:31.360
From my younger days, you always made me pretty and my figure, since you understand all my angles.

488
00:41:31.360 --> 00:41:35.140
No matter what the angles are, you're pretty.

